text: We will hear next in 76-1057 Key against Doyle.
Mr. Chief Justice may it please the court.
Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the court.
Oh yes your honor I want to just brief on --
Whether he is going to give us anything?

Just on the issue of jurisdiction, I submit that what my brother says is not accurate because the Statute would not include the last paragraph that is 1257 would not include the last paragraph, if Congress did not mean for the State, this Court to have Appellate Jurisdiction over the District of Columbia Court of Appeals.
